i was sitting at the fireplace having a smoke with all of the lights out.  the fire was bright because i kept feeding it ink laced oxygen for several minutes already, and under a very dry log from back in the storage shed.

[the same shed of the famous spider war of 2015, at my house. my house that is for sale, and you can make me move on zillow for $550k. port orchard bound, unless I change my mind. and my kids know i like to change my mind. they call it lying, but i call it honesty.]

she was sitting on the couch with her boyfriend at the moment, and we started writing, ghostscript.

ghostscript (the other postscript), where i hold the pen and she moves it around from across the room. actually, now it's just from across the street, but whatever.....

we were writing an epic poem.  i tore out the first page, put a ring in the middle of it. a ring that i wore on my ring finger the whole time i shredded haderslev with mr. magnus, the other author on here.

i bought it for her in copenhagen. it came with two 15th street christmas tree earrings, and two infinity symbol earrings, but those went elsewhere to the way way wayyyy side.

(traded them for sugar cookies)

i don't know what happened to that ring to this day.  i think it's lost in the ugliest couch in the world, or in a pawn shop.  it was a lovely 12 pointed star.

when her boyfriend sat back down, i kicked him out and smoked all of the smokes i gave him.

she sat down by me in front of the fire. her "boyfriend" STILL sat on the couch. i let him. i wasn't taking his girl. she liked him, not me. duh. she's her own person. and i'm more than grateful to have penned in her hand.

boundaries continued to cross. ugh.

like a spider webbed in a  perfect cocoon.

a cocoon that she wanted. It makes sense.

however, there was one small moment we touched, with her "boyfriend" on the couch, not taking notice to SHIT (quite the actor, indeed).

the cells in our body breached our skin. i feel if we touched any longer, we could make great shapes to shift together.

i didn't know these kinds of people existed.  and i'm blind as a goddamn bat.

it's how i can skate like a bat so well when there are no lights at marginal way.  so make a donation today. we need solar.

